    "narrative": "The Zurich Zebras enter today\u2019s slate with a lineup anchored by **Christian Yelich** and **Trea Turner**, who emerge as our top options with efficiency scores of 72.61 and 71.43, respectively. **Christian Yelich** benefits from a massive 13% dynamic platoon boost and a favorable matchup against Littell, making him our primary offensive engine. Meanwhile, **Trea Turner** maintains his status as an elite play despite facing a stiff test in Gallen; his spot at the top of the order and the associated volume remain the highest floor in our 5x5 build. High-scoring support comes from **Kyle Schwarber** (67.82) and **Caleb Durbin** (67.85), both of whom are buoyed by an anticipated wind-out effect and the aggressive baserunning environment presented by today\u2019s opposing batteries.\n\nThe most difficult decision on the bench involved **Victor Scott II**, whose 58.31 score fell just short of **Kazuma Okamoto** (58.71) and **Pete Crow-Armstrong** (61.24). While **Victor Scott II** offers the high-upside speed we covet, his placement in the 9-hole severely dampened his efficiency, forcing the algorithm to prioritize the higher lineup spots held by **Chase Meidroth** and **Junior Caminero**. We are monitoring the risk profile of **Yordan Alvarez**, whose score of 53.98 is suppressed by a brutal matchup against Gilbert. While his raw talent is undeniable, he is trending toward a \"marginal\" start; however, given his elite xwOBA, we are keeping him active to avoid leaving production on the bench. Conversely, while **Dillon Dingler** is currently sub-50, his matchup against Alcantara suggests a slow-delivery environment that may create opportunistic stolen base windows, keeping him in the lineup despite his modest baseline projection.",
